The truncated SUDc5b binds efficiently (K
d = 0.45 μM) to an oligodeoxynucleotide (named bbc3-(dG)14) of 24 bases in length, with a central (dG)14 stretch, which we used as a model for the bbc3 mRNA. The replacement of the (dG)14 stretch by (dA)14 leads to a dramatically reduced binding affinity (Fig. 3
). Similar results were obtained for full-length SUD (not shown).
